<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-100-034 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 049 700</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computergram International  July 29 1991 n1727* Full Text COPYRIGHT Apt Data Services (UK) 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Baby Bells freed to offer electronic data services. (Bell regionalholding companies)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Telephone companiesBell Regional Holding CompaniesDeregulationCompetitionInformation servicesGovernment Regulation.andO;Person:    Greene, Harold (Science and technology policy).andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>BABY BELLS FREED TO OFFER ELECTRONIC DATA SERVICESandM;A dismayed Judge Harold Greene is seeing his antitrust settlement with ATandamp;TCo and the Baby Bells slowly slipping away from him, and he has reluctantlygranted the seven regional telephone companies spun out from ATandamp;T permissionto participate in the electronic information business by providing servicessuch as audiotext, viewdata, home shopping and stock market quotes.andP;  He wasforced into his ruling by an appellate court ruling that reversed his 1987decision on the issues, but made clear his dismay, saying he believed thatletting the companies enter the information market &quot;would allow them quicklyto dominate that market and to eliminate both competition and theindependents which would make that competition possible.&quot; The JusticeDepartment joined the Bells in asking Judge Greene to allow them to use theirtelephone lines to offer their own on-line services.andO;</TEXT></DOC>